              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COIN",
                "SIBAR",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A pair of silicon surface-barrier",
                "semiconductor counters. One of these counters",
                "detected one of the two fission fragments. The other",
                "counter (covered with a 6.2-mg/cm2 aluminum foil to",
                "stop all fission fragments) detected charged",
                "particles in coincidence with fission."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Thin targets of natural uranium and thorium. The",
                "targets consisted of uranium or thorium oxide. The",
                "targets were everywhere thinner than 0.5 mg/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The number of alpha particles per fission was",
                "determined from measurements taken with the alpha",
                "particle and fission counters at 135 degrees on",
                "opposite sides of the beam. The over-all",
                "alpha/fission ratios were deduced from a comparison",
                "with a standard Cf252 source.",
                "In order to convert the measured ratio of (long-range",
                "alpha-fission coincidences): (total fission counts in",
                "the same time interval) into a useful number, the ratio",
                "was divided by the same ratio measured for a Cf252",
                "spontaneous fission source under identical conditions.",
                "The result was then multiplied by the known number of",
                "alpha particles per fission for Cf252, 3.35e-03."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
